id: pm-hous
title: "GH-514: pm init writes no .gitignore rules — runtime/search caches churn as tracked files in downstream repos"
description: "GH-514 reports pm init writing a malformed .gitignore line concatenating .agents/pm/search/ + .agents/pm/runtime/metadata-cache-bodies.json. Source evidence: the block header string ('PM CLI runtime and cache files') has NEVER existed in this repo history (git log -S empty; zero hits in src/dist/packages/plugins) — pm init currently writes NO .gitignore entries at all. The malformed block in the reporting repo (simworld) was authored by external tooling. The real defect this issue surfaces: because pm init owns no ignore rules, repos that version .agents/pm get spurious churn on runtime/metadata-cache*.json and search/ caches with every command, and users/agents hand-write (and garble) ignore blocks. Fix = pm init owns a canonical idempotent fenced block + a health/validate check for already-tracked cache files. Related: pm-4det (this repo untracked its own caches), GH-501/pm-69nl (init discovery)."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: dx,gh-issue,init,onboarding
